http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/other-states/%E2%80%98We-will-take-care-of-Bundelkhand%E2%80%99/article14006053.ece

With the Opposition parties getting active in the Bundelkhand region of Uttar Pradesh in the run up to the 2017 Assembly polls, Chief Minister Akhilesh Yadav on Monday said his government would make necessary efforts to address the issues the area confronts.After a Cabinet meeting, Mr Yadav said Chief Secretary Alok Ranjan recently visited the region to take stock of the development scheme and he would visit Bundelkhand.“We have taken a decision on the works to be carried out under MNREGA... In coming times, I’ll also visit Bundelkhand. My government will help the region in every possible way,” he said.The statement comes at a time when Congress vice-president Rahul Gandhi is scheduled to visit Bundelkhand on January 22.“As far as Bundelkhand is concerned, you must remember that the SP and its government were the first to take care of the region,” he claimed.Bundelkhand comprises parts of Uttar Pradesh and Madhya Pradesh. -- PTI